('', '1', 0, 1, 0, 'milliarda', 'milliarda', 'numeral', 'numeral', 'billion (thousand million)', 'billion, thousand million', 'milliarda', 'milliarda', 'miliarda', 'miliarda', 'milliarda', 'milliarda', 'milliard (m)', 'milliard', 'milliard (m)', 'milliard', 'Billion:\n\"Billion\" in the American sense of 1 000 000 000 (now generally adopted throughout the English-speaking world) is \"milliarda\" in Romansh. The Romansh \"billiun\" corresponds to an American \"trillion\" or \"thousand billion\" (or the older English billion) i.e. 1 000 000 000 000.', 'Migliarda/billiun:\nStar attent:\nIl pled \"milliard\" n\'exista betg en englais normal.\nIsotricamain era in billiun englais britannic il medem sco in billiun rumantsch (1 000 000 000 000).\nEn l\'America dal nord signifitgescha in billiun gia dapi ditg il medem sco ina migliarda rumantscha (1 000 000 000). L\'adiever britannic sa sviluppa era en quest senn, ma i dat anc surtut glieud veglia en la Gronda Britannia che fa adiever dal billiun en il senn tradiziunal.\nPer evitar embrugls, èsi savens meglier da far adiever dals terms segirs \"thousand million\" u \"million million\".', '', '', '', 290),
