('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'avair', 'avair', 'verb', 'verb', 'have', 'have, have got, \'ve, had', 'haver', 'haver', 'adaver, aver, ver', 'aver, adaver, ver, vessan', 'aveir', 'aveir', 'avair', 'avair', 'avair', 'avair', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"avair\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv: have\nPreschent: I/we/you/they have, he/she/it has\nPassà simpel: had\nParticip: had\nEn il senn da \"posseder\" vegn il verb \"have\" en englais savens duvrà cun \"got\": \"Jau hai ina fitg gronda famiglia.\" = \"I\'ve got a very big family\".\n\"Have\" vegn savens scursanì sin \"\'ve\" e \"has\" sin \"\'s\".', '', 'AVAIR\n\nPreschent: \njau hai\nti has\nel/ella/ins ha\nnus avain\nvus avais\nels/ellas han \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a avair \nti vegns a avair \nel/ella/ins vegn a avair \nnus vegnin a avair \nvus vegnis a avair \nels/ellas vegnan a avair \n\nImperfect: \njau aveva\nti avevas\nel/ella/ins aveva\nnus avevan\nvus avevas\nels/ellas avevan \n\nParticip perfect: \ngì \n\nPerfect:\njau hai gì\nti has gì\nel/ella/ins ha gì\nnus avain gì\nvus avais gì\nels/ellas han gì \n\nCundiziunal: \njau avess\nti avessas\nel/ella/ins avess\nnus avessan\nvus avessas\nels/ellas avessan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau haja\nche ti hajas\nch\'el/ella/ins haja\nche nus hajan\nche vus hajas\nch\'els/ellas hajan\n\nImperativ: \n hajas!\nhajas! \n\nGerundi: \navend', '', 352),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'esser', 'esser', 'verb', 'verb', 'be', 'be, am, are, is, was, were, I\'m, been', 'esser', 'esser', 'easser', 'easser', 'esser', 'esser', 'esser', 'esser', 'esser', 'esser', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"esser\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nNote that there are many expressions in which a verb other than \"esser\" corresponds to the English \"be\".', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv: (to) be\nPreschent: I am, he/she/it is, we/you/they are\nPassà simpel: I/he/she/it was, we/you/they were\nParticip: been\nA nudar: la furma interrogativa: aren\'t I?', '', 'ESSER\n\nPreschent: \njau sun\nti es\nel/ella/ins è\nnus essan\nvus essas\nels/ellas èn \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a esser \nti vegns a esser \nel/ella/ins vegn a esser \nnus vegnin a esser \nvus vegnis a esser \nels/ellas vegnan a esser\n\nImperfect: \njau era\nti eras\nel/ella/ins era\nnus eran\nvus eras\nels/ellas eran \n\nParticip perfect:\nstà (f.: stada, mpl: stads, fpl: stadas)\n\nPerfect: \njau sun stà/stada\nti es stà/stada\nel/ella/ins è stà/stada\nnus essan stads/stadas\nvus essas stads/stadas\nels/ellas èn stads/stadas\n\nCundiziunal: \njau fiss\nti fissas\nel/ella/ins fiss\nnus fissan\nvus fissas\nels/ellas fissan\n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau saja\nche ti sajas\nch\'el/ella/ins saja\nche nus sajan\nche vus sajas\nch\'els/ellas sajan \n\nImperativ: \nsajas!\nsajas! \n\nGerundi: \nessend/siond', '', 353),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'star', 'star', 'verb', 'verb', 'be, stay, live, etc.', 'be, stay, live', 'star', 'star', 'star', 'star, stun, stagn', 'star', 'star', 'abiter, ster', 'ster', 'star', 'star', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"star\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\n\"Star\" means live in the sense of living in or inhabiting a place. Live in the sense of being alice is \"viver\".', '', '', 'STAR \n\nPreschent: \njau stun \nti stas \nel/ella/ins stat \nnus stain \nvus stais \nels/ellas stattan \n\nFutur: \njau vegn a star \nti vegns a star \nel/ella/ins vegn a star \nnus vegnin a star \nvus vegnis a star \nels/ellas vegnan a star\n\nImperfect: \njau steva \nti stevas \nel/ella/ins steva \nnus stevan \nvus stevas \nels/ellas stevan \n\nParticip perfect: \n// stà (f.: stada, mpl.: stads, fpl.: stadas)\n\nPerfect: \njau sun stà/stada\nti es stà/stada\nel/ella/ins è stà/stada\nnus essan stads/stadas\nvus essas stads/stadas\nels/ellas èn stads/stadas\n\nCundiziunal: \njau stess \nti stessas \nel/ella/ins stess \nnus stessan \nvus stessas \nels/ellas stessan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau stettia \nche ti stettias \nch\'el/ella/ins stettia \nche nus stettian \nche vus stettias \nch\'els/ellas stettian  / \nImperativ: \nsta! \nstai! \n\n Gerundi: \nstond', '', 354),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'vegnir', 'vegnir', 'verb', 'verb', 'come', 'come, came', 'vegnir', 'vegnir', 'vagnir', 'vagnir, vignt, nus vagnagn', 'neir', 'neir', 'gnir', 'gnir, vain', 'gnir', 'gnir, vain, vegn', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"vegnir\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nThe verb \"vegnir\" is very busy in Romansh.\nIts first meaning is \"come\".\nSecondly, it can mean \"become\" (with daventar\" available as an alternative).\nThirdly, it is used as the auxiliary for the passive mood.\nFourthly, it is used to form the normal future tense (in combination with a + the infinitive) in the standardised language and three of the idioms (Puter and Vallader have an inflected future tense. Surmiran has both forms).', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv/preschent: come\nPassà simpel: came\nParticip: come', '', 'VEGNIR \n\nPreschent: \njau vegn\nti vegns\nel/ella/ins vegn\nnus vegnin\nvus vegnis\nels/ellas vegnan \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a vegnir \nti vegns a vegnir \nel/ella/ins vegn a vegnir \nnus vegnin a vegnir \nvus vegnis a vegnir \nels/ellas vegnan a vegnir \n\nImperfect: \njau vegniva\nti vegnivas\nel/ella/ins vegniva\nnus vegnivan\nvus vegnivas\nels/ellas vegnivan \n\nParticip perfect: \nvegnì (f: vegnida, mpl: vegnids, fpl: vegnidas)\n\nPerfect:\nJau sun vegnì/ vegnida\nTi es vegnì/ vegnida\nel/ella/ins è vegnì/vegnida\nnus essan vegnids/vegnidas\nvus essas vegnids/vegnidas\nels/ellas èn vegnids/vegnidas\n\nCundiziunal: \njau vegniss\nti vegnissas\nel/ella/ins vegniss\nnus vegnissan\nvus vegnissas\nels/ellas vegnissan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau vegnia\nche ti vegnias\nch\'el/ella/ins vegnia\nche nus vegnian\nche vus vegnias\nch\'els/ellas vegnian \n\nImperativ: \nve!\nvegni! \n\nGerundi: \nvegnind ', '', 355),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, '* Guardar las Remartgas. *\n* See Comments. *', '', '-----', 'verb', 'get', 'get, got, gotten', '-----', '', '-----', '', '-----', '', '-----', '', '-----', '', 'Get:\n\"Get\" has dozens of different meanings in English, and many of them are included in this dictionary. We suggest that you try searching on the basis a fuller expression (get in, get out, get up, etc.) or on the basis of a synonym.', 'Englais: \"get\":\n\"Get\" è in dals verbs pli universals en englais. El vegn duvrà sulet u en cumbinaziun cun in auter pled (normalmain ina preposiziun u in adverb).\nSia muntada pli simpla è \"survegnir\"/\"retschaiver\".\nEl serva savens sco sinonim per \"become\" (daventar/vegnir):\n\"Jau vegn vegl\" = \"I\'m getting old\".\nQuest pledari cuntegna plirs exempels da cumbinaziuns cun \"get\". Per als vesair in suenter l\'auter, endatar \"get \" e \"proxim\".\n\"Get\" è irregular:\nPassà simpel: got\nParticip passà: got / gotten\n(Surtut ils americans fan diever da \"gotten\".)', 'I\'m getting older. = Jau vegn pli vegl.\nI got a bike for my birthday. = Jau hai survegnì in velo per mes anniversari.\nShe got off the bus and (got) onto the train. = Ella è sortida dal bus ed ida en il tren.\nHe got freightened by the thunder. = Il tun ha fatg tema ad el.', '', '', 356),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'far', 'far, fatg', 'verb', 'verb', 'do, make', 'do, make, did, made, does, doesn\'t, don\'t, didn\'t', 'far', 'far, fatg', 'far', 'far, fagiagn, fetsch, fatg, fani, faged', 'far', 'far', 'fer', 'fer', 'far', 'far', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"far\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nNote that Romansh does not make any distinction between \"do\" and \"make\".', 'Verbs irregulars englais.\n(1)\nInfinitiv: do\nPreschent: I/we/you/they do, he/she/it does\nPassà simpel: did\nParticip: done\n(2)\nInfinitv/preschent: make\nPassà simpel: made\nParticip: made\n// Ina da las pli grondas difficultads per glieud ch\'emprenda englais è da distinguer tranter \"do\" e \"make\", domadus signifitgeschan \"far\" en rumantsch. Il \"tun\" tudestg è normalmain \"do\". Il \"machen\" tudestg po esser \"do\" u \"make\".\nLas differentas furmas da \"do\" vegnan normalmain cumbinadas cun il negativ \"not\": \"don\'t\", \"doesn\'t\", \"didn\'t\".', '', 'FAR\n\nPreschent:\njau fatsch\nti fas\nel/ella/ins fa\nnus faschain\nvus faschais\nels/ellas fan \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a far\nti vegns a far\nel/ella/ins vegn a far\nnus vegnin a far\nvus vegnis a far\nels/ellas vegnan a far \n\nImperfect:\njau fascheva\nti faschevas\nel/ella/ins fascheva\nnus faschevan\nvus faschevas\nels/ellas faschevan\n\nParticip perfect\nfatg (f: fatga, mpl: fatgs, fpl: fatgas)\n\nPerfect:\njau hai fatg\nti has fatg\nel/ella/ins ha fatg\nnus avain fatg\nvus avais fatg\nels/ellas han fatg\n\nCundiziunal:\njau faschess\nti faschessas\nel/ella/ins faschess\nnus faschessan\nvus faschessas\nels/ellas faschessan\n\nConjunctiv:\nche jau fetschia\nche ti fetschias\nch\'el/ella/ins fetschia\nche nus fetschian\nche vus fetschias\nch\'els/ellas fetschian\n\nImperativ:\nfa!\nfaschai!\n\nGerundi:\nfaschond', '', 357),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'dar', 'dar', 'verb', 'verb', 'give', 'give, gave, given', 'dar', 'dar', 'dar', 'dar, dund, dagn', 'dar', 'dar', 'der', 'der', 'dar', 'dar', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"dar\"\nTo view full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nNote that \"dar\" can also mean \"play\" in Romansh. It is also used in many idiomatic expressions where a different verb is required in English.', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv/preschent: give\nPassà simpel: gave\nParticip: given', '', 'DAR \n\nPreschent: \njau dun\nti das\nel/ella/ins dat\nnus dain\nvus dais\nels/ellas dattan\n\nFutur:\njau vegn a dar \nti vegns a dar \nel/ella/ins vegn a dar \nnus vegnin a dar \nvus vegnis a dar \nels/ellas vegnan a dar \n\nImperfect: \njau deva\nti devas\nel/ella/ins deva\nnus devan\nvus devas\nels/ellas devan\n\nParticip perfect: \ndà (f: dada, mpl: dads, fpl: dadas)\n\nPerfect: \njau hai dà\nti has dà\nel/ellas/ins ha dà\nnus avain dà\nvus avais dà\nels/ellas han dà\n\nCundiziunal: \njau dess\nti dessas\nel/ella/ins dess\nnus dessan\nvus dessas\nels/ellas dessan\n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau dettia\nche ti dettias\nch\'el/ella/ins dettia\nche nus dettian\nche vus dettias\nch\'els/ellas dettian\n\nImperativ: \ndà!\ndai!\n\nGerundi: \ndend \n\n', '', 358);
