('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'ir', 'ir, va', 'verb', 'verb', 'go', 'goes, gone, went', 'ir', 'ir, va, mon, vas, va, mein, meis, van; iu, ida', 'ir', 'ir, vont, nus nagn, va nad', 'eir', 'eir', 'ir', 'ir', 'ir', 'ir', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"ir\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\n Note, in particular, the Romansh expression \"i va\" (= it\'s ok, things are fine).', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv: go\nPreschent: I/we/you/they go, he/she/it goes\nPassà simpel: went\nParticip: gone (enstagl da \"gone\" fan ins savens adiever da \"been\" surtut en il senn da visitar lieus). ', '', 'IR \n\nPreschent:\njau vom\nti vas\nel/ella/ins va\nnus giain\nvus giais\nels/ellas van \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a ir \nti vegns a ir \nel/ella/ins vegn a ir \nnus vegnin a ir \nvus vegnis a ir \nels/ellas vegnan a ir\n\nImperfect:\njau gieva\nti gievas\nel/ella/ins gieva\nnus gievan\nvus gievas\nels/ellas gievan \n\nParticip perfect: \nì (f: ida, mpl: ids, fpl: idas)\n\nPerfect:\njau sun ì/ida\nti es ì/ida\nel/ella/ins è ì/ida\nnus essan ids/idas \nvus essas ids/idas\nels/ellas èn ids/idas \n\nCundiziunal: \njau giess\nti giessas\nel/ella/ins giess\nnus giessan\nvus giessas\nels/ellas giessan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau giaja\nche ti giajas\nch\'el/ella/ins giaja\nche nus giajan\nche vus giajas\nch\'els/ellas giajan\n\nImperativ: \nva!\ngiai! \n\nGerundi: \ngiond', '', 359),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'gugent', 'gugent', 'adverb', 'adverb', 'willingly', 'like, willingly', 'bugen', 'bugen', 'bugent', 'bugent', 'gugent', 'gugent', 'gugent', 'gugent', 'gugent, jent', 'gugent, jent', 'Liking, loving, preferring (01):\nThe adverb \"gugent\" (which has no direct equivalent in modern English) is used in combination with \"avair\" for liking people or things and in combination with \"far\" or many other verbs for liking doing things.\nExamples(1):\nJau hai tai gugent = I love you.\n(2) Jau fatsch gugent pensums = / I like doing homework.\n(3) Jau nod gugent = I like swimming.', '', '', '', '', 360),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'avair gugent', 'avair gugent', 'verb', 'verb', 'love', 'love', 'haver bugen', 'haver bugen', 'aver bugent', 'aver bugent', 'aveir gugent', 'aveir gugent', 'avair gugent', 'avair gugent, avair jent', 'avair gugent, avair jent', 'avair gugent, avair jent', 'Liking, loving, preferring (02):\nThe adverb \"gugent\" (which has no direct equivalent in modern English) is used in combination with \"avair\" for liking people or things and in combination with \"far\" or many other verbs for liking doing things.\nExamples(1):\nJau hai tai gugent = I love you.\n(2) Jau fatsch gugent pensums = / I like doing homework.\n(3) Jau nod gugent = I like swimming.', '', '', '', '', 361),
('', '1', 1, 1, 0, 'far gugent', 'far gugent', 'verb', 'verb', 'like, love', 'like, love', 'far bugen', 'far bugen', 'far bugent', 'far bugent', 'far gugent', 'far gugent', 'fer gugent', 'fer gugent', 'far gugent', 'far gugent', 'Liking, loving, preferring (03):\nThe adverb \"gugent\" (which has no direct equivalent in modern English) is used in combination with \"avair\" for liking people or things and in combination with \"far\" or many other verbs for liking doing things.', '', '(1) Ella sauta gugent. = She loves dancing.\n(2) El va gugent cun velo. = He likes cycling.\n(3) Jau hai tai gugent = I love you.\n(4) Jau fatsch gugent pensums = I like doing homework.', '', '', 362),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'star', 'star', 'verb', 'verb', 'stand up', 'stand', 'star', 'star', 'star', 'star, stun, stagn', 'star', 'star', 'ster (in pè)', 'ster', 'star', 'star', '', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv/preschent: stand\nPassà simpel: stood\nParticip: stood', '', '', '', 363),
('', '1', 1, 1, 0, 'ura', 'ura', 'num feminin', 'noun', 'time, clock times', 'time, clocktimes, clock times', 'ura', 'ura', 'ura', 'ura', 'oura', 'oura', 'ura', 'ura', 'ura', 'ura', 'Time:\nThe general-purpose word for \"time\" in Romansh is \"temp\".\n\"Ura\" (which also means \"hour\") is used for the time on the clock.\n\"Peda\" is used for having time available to do something.\nTo have time for something is \"avair temp\" or \"avair peda\". But there is a big difference! \"Avair temp\" simply means having a spare slot in one\'s diary. \"Avair peda\" means finding time or making time available for a commitment. (Sometimes the two words are combined: \"Avais temp e peda?\" (Do you have time for...\")\nNote the saying: \"I dat bain umans che han ina massa temp, mo nagina peda.\" (\"There are people with plenty of time to spare, but never any time to really do anything.\")', '', '', '', '', 364),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'be, mo', 'be, mo', 'adverb', 'adverb', 'only, just', 'only', 'mo', 'mo', 'me', 'me', 'angal', 'angal', 'be', 'be', 'be', 'be', '', '', '(1) Jau sun mo in pau stanchel. =\nI\'m just a bit tired.\n(2) Jau m\'hai mo dumandà. = I just wondered.', '', '', 365),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'tegnair', 'tegnair', 'verb', 'verb', 'hold, keep', 'hold, keep', 'tener', 'tener', 'taner', 'taner', 'tigneir', 'tigneir, tignan', 'tgnair', 'tgnair', 'tgnair', 'tgnair', 'Romansh verbs (4);\nRegular verbs with an infinitive in \"-air\":\n\"Tegnair\" is one of these.\nTo view its full conjugation, click \" Details\".', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv/preschent: hold\nPassà simpel: held\nParticip: held', '', 'TEGNAIR \n\nPreschent:\njau tegn\nti tegnas\nel/ella/ins tegna\nnus tegnain\nvus tegnais\nels/ellas tegnan \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a tegnair \nti vegns a tegnair \nel/ella/ins vegn a tegnair \nnus vegnin a tegnair \nvus vegnis a tegnair \nels/ellas vegnan a tegnair\n\nImperfect:\njau tegneva\nti tegnevas\nel/ella/ins tegneva\nnus tegnevan\nvus tegnevas\nels/ellas tegnevan \n\nParticip perfect: \ntegnì (f: tegnida, mpl: tegnids. fpl: tegnidas)\n\nPerfect:\njau hai tegnì\nti has tegnì\nel/ella/ins ha tegnì\nnus avain tegnì\nvus avais tegnì\nels/ellas han tegnì\n\nCundiziunal: \njau tegness\nti tegnessas\nel/ella/ins tegness\nnus tegnessan\nvus tegnessas\nels/ellas tegnessan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau tegnia\nche ti tegnias\nch\'el/ella/ins tegnia\nche nus tegnian\nche vus tegnias\nch\'els/ellas tegnian\n\nImperativ: \ntegna!\ntegnai!\nGerundi:\ntegnend', '', 366),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'savair', 'savair', 'verb', 'verb', 'know', 'know, knew, known', 'saver', 'saver', 'saver', 'saver, se, savagn', 'saveir', 'saveir', 'savair', 'savair, So\'L', 'savair', 'savair, sa\'L', 'Know (1):\n\"Know\" is the sense of knowing how to do something. is \"savair\" (an irregular verb). \"Know\" in the sense of being acquainted with is \"(en)conuscher\". It is important to make this distinction.', 'Verb irregular englais:\nInfinitiv/preschent: know\nPassà simpel: knew\nParticip: known\nPronunzia:\nTar pleds englais ch\'entschaivan cun \"kn\" è il \"k\" mit.', '', '', '', 367),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'pudair', 'pudair', 'verb', 'verb', 'can, be able to', 'can, be able to, cannot, can\'t', 'puder', 'puder', 'puder', 'puder, pos, pudagn', 'pudeir', 'pudeir, po', 'pudair', 'pudair', 'pudair', 'pudair', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"Pudair\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".', 'Englais \"can\":\nQuest verb è incumplet. Per quellas parts che n\'existan betg, dovr\'ins per exempel parts da \"to be able to\".\nEn la furma negativa vegn \"can\" normalmain cumbinà cun \"not\" per far in sulet pled: \"cannot\". En il linguatg pledà vegn quai scursanì sin \"can\'t\".', 'Pos ti nudar? = Can you swim?', 'PUDAIR \n\nPreschent:\njau poss\nti pos\nel/ella/ins po\nnus pudain\nvus pudais\nels/ellas pon \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a pudair \nti vegns a pudair \nel/ella/ins vegn a pudair \nnus vegnin a pudair \nvus vegnis a pudair \nels/ellas vegnan a pudair \n\nImperfect:\njau pudeva\nti pudevas\nel/ella/ins pudeva\nnus pudevan\nvus pudevas\nels/ellas pudevan \n\nParticip perfect: \npudì (f: pudida, mpl: pudids, fpl: pudidas) \n\nPerfect:\njau hai pudì\nti has pudì\nel/ella/ins ha pudì\nnus avain pudì\nvus avais pudì\nels/ellas han pudì\n\nCundiziunal: \njau pudess\nti pudessas\nel/ella/ins pudess\nnus pudessan\nvus pudessas\nels/ellas pudessan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau possia\nche ti possias\nch\'el/ella/ins possia\nche nus possian\nche vus possias\nch\'els/ellas possian\n\nImperativ: \n-----\n----- \n\nGerundi: \npudend  //', '', 368),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'vegnir a', 'vegnir', 'verb', 'verb', 'will, shall', 'will, shall, won\'t', 'vegnir a', 'vegnir a', 'vagnir a', 'vagnir a', 'neir a', 'neir a', '* Guardar las Remartgas. / See Comments *', '', '* Guardar las Remartgas. / See Comments *', '', 'Romansh verbs (1):\nIrregular verbs:\nThere are several dozen of these, including \"vegnir\"\nTo view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nThe verb \"vegnir\" is very busy in Romansh.\nIts first meaning is \"come\".\nSecondly, it can mean \"become\" (with daventar\" available as an alternative).\nThirdly, it is used as the auxiliary for the passive mood.\nFourthly, it is used to form the normal future tense (in combination with a + the infinitive) in the standardised language and three of the idioms (Puter and Vallader have an inflected future tense. Surmiran has both forms).', 'Futur en englais:\nIl futur normal en il englais pledà è simplamain \"\'ll\". Ozendi scriv\'ins er per la plipart \"\'ll\" (a l\'excepziun da texts d\'ina natira formala).\nNoviz(a)s d\'englais san emblidar la furma \"shall\" dal futur e far diever da \"will\" en tut ils cas.\nSpezialistas/spezialists stuessan dentant enconuscher il suandant:\nGia il diever da \"will\" enstagl da \"\'ll\" dat in tschert pais.\nEn l\'emprima persuna exprima \"will\" in intent pli ferm che \"shall\".\nEn la segunda e terza persuna exprima \"shall\" bunamain in urden e correspunda a \"must\" (surtut en texts da leschas).\nAdatg: igl è meglier dad evitar quest \"shall\" dal tuttafatg che dad al duvrar fauss!\nIl negativ usità da \"will\" è \"won\'t\".\n', '', 'VEGNIR \n\nPreschent: \njau vegn\nti vegns\nel/ella/ins vegn\nnus vegnin\nvus vegnis\nels/ellas vegnan \n\nFutur:\njau vegn a vegnir \nti vegns a vegnir \nel/ella/ins vegn a vegnir \nnus vegnin a vegnir \nvus vegnis a vegnir \nels/ellas vegnan a vegnir \n\nImperfect: \njau vegniva\nti vegnivas\nel/ella/ins vegniva\nnus vegnivan\nvus vegnivas\nels/ellas vegnivan \n\nParticip perfect: \nvegnì (f: vegnida, mpl: vegnids, fpl: vegnidas)\n\nPerfect:\nJau sun vegnì/ vegnida\nTi es vegnì/ vegnida\nel/ella/ins è vegnì/vegnida\nnus essan vegnids/vegnidas\nvus essas vegnids/vegnidas\nels/ellas èn vegnids/vegnidas\n\nCundiziunal: \njau vegniss\nti vegnissas\nel/ella/ins vegniss\nnus vegnissan\nvus vegnissas\nels/ellas vegnissan \n\nConjunctiv: \nche jau vegnia\nche ti vegnias\nch\'el/ella/ins vegnia\nche nus vegnian\nche vus vegnias\nch\'els/ellas vegnian \n\nImperativ: \nve!\nvegni! \n\nGerundi: \nvegnind ', '', 369),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'svizzer\n(f: svizra)', 'svizzer, svizra', 'adjectiv', 'adjective', 'Swiss', 'Swiss', 'svizzer (f: sivzra)', 'svizzer, sivzra', 'svizer (f: svizra)', 'svizer, svizra', 'svizzer (f: sivzra)', 'svizzer, sivzra', 'svizzer (f: sivzra)', 'svizzer, sivzra', 'svizzer (f: sivzra)', 'svizzer, sivzra', 'Adjectives of nationality, etc. are generally written with a small letter in Romansh.', 'Adjectivs da naziunalitad, euv.:\nQuels vegnan adina scrits cun in bustab grond en englais.', '', '', '', 370),
