('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'na... betg, n\' betg', 'betg, na, nun', 'adverb', 'adverb', 'not', 'not', 'buc, buca', 'buc, buca', 'betg, betga', 'betg, betga', 'nabetg', 'betg', 'nu, nun', 'nu, nun', 'nu, nun', 'nu, nun', 'Negatives:\nWith verbs, the usual negative in Rumantsch Grischun is in two parts: \"na\" (or \"n\'\") before the verb and \"betg\" after it. In expressions without a verb, the negative is usually just \"betg\".\nNote that some of the idioms use just their equivalent of \"betg\" after the verb without the \"na\" before it, whereas others use just one word, \"nun\", before the verb. These practices are sometimes also encountered in Rumantsch Grischun, but are now considered as wrong.', '', '', '', '', 372),
('', '1', 1, 1, 0, '-----', '', 'preposiziun + artitgel', 'preposition + article', 'for the', '', 'pil, pigl (f: pella, pell\', mpl: pils, fpl: pellas)', 'pil, pigl, pils, pella, pell\' pellas', 'pigl (f: par la, mpl: pigls, fpl: par las)', 'pigl, pigls', 'pigl (f: per la, mpl: pigls, f: per las)', 'pigl, pigls', 'per (f: per la, mpl: pels, fpl: per las)', 'pel, pels, pella, pellas', 'per (f: pella, mpl: pels, fpl: pellas)', 'per, pella, pels, pellas', 'Prepositions combined with definite articles in Romansh:\nA few common Romansh prepositions are merged with the following definite article to form a single word. The extent of this phenomenon varies from one idiom of the language to another. It occurs least in standardised Rumantsch Grischun.', '', '', '', '', 373),
