('', '1', 1, 1, 0, '* Guardar las Remartgas. *\n* See Comments. *', 'sa, s\'', '..', '..', '* Guardar las Remartgas. *\n* See Comments. *', '', '(=RG)', 'se, s\'', '(=RG)', 'sa, s\'', '(=RG)', 'sa, s\'', '(=RG)', 'as', '(=RG)', 'as', 'Reflexive verbs:\nHundreds of these are used regularly in Romansh, and countless others can be made reflexive as required. Often they have a nuance of meaning that is more than \"doing something to oneself\". Each one is explained individually in this dictionary. The accusative pronoun comes BEFORE the verb (as in French, Italian, etc.). In the infinitive, this is \"sa\" (\"s\'\" before vowels) in Rumantsch Grischun, Sutsilvan and Surmiran, \"se...\" or \"s\'\" in Sursilvan and \"as\" in Puter and Vallader . In Rumantsch Grischun and the majority of the idioms, the pronoun changes according to the person (Rumantsch Grischun, for instance: ma (m\'), ta (t\'), sa (s\'), ans, as, sa (s\')). In Sursilvan and Sutsilvan the \"se\"/\"sa\"/\"s\'\", which is joined up to the verb, is invariable whatever the person.', '', '', '', '', 377),
('', '1', 1, 1, 1, 'rumantsch', 'rumantsch, rumantscha', 'adjectiv', 'adjective', 'Romansh', 'Romansh, Romansch, rumantsch, romontsch, rumauntsch, rumàntsch, rumantscah, romontscha, rumauntscha, rumàntscha, Swiss Romansh, Swiss Romance, Rhaeto-Romansh, Rhaeto-Romance, Raeto-Romansh, Raeto-Romance, Reto-Romansh, Reto-Romance', 'romontsch', 'romontsch, romontscha', 'rumàntsch', 'rumàntsch, rumàntscha', 'rumantsch', 'rumantsch', 'rumauntsch', 'rumauntsch', 'rumantsch', 'rumantsch, rumantsch', 'Romansh:\nThe language.\nUp to a dozen different terms and spellings are to be found in texts written in English. The myPledari compilers have examined these in terms of their frequency and credibility. In agreement with the Lia Rumantscha, we should like to urge everyone to use \"Romansh\" as the standard English spelling (and to abandon all other forms). As an alternative, it is also acceptable to use the word \"Rumantsch\" itself in English.\nFor greater precision in scientific texts, some linguists prefer the term \"Swiss Romansh\" or \"Swiss Romance\".\nThe term \"R(h)aeto-Romance\" is sometimes limited to Graubünden and sometimes taken to include Dolomitic Ladin and Friulian too.', 'Rumantsch:\nEn englais chatt\'ins plirs terms per \"rumantsch\".\n\"Romansh\" è il pli usità per il mintgadi.\nIns sa era far adiever dal term \"Rumantsch\" en englais.', '', '', '', 378),
