('', '1', 1, 0, 1, 'clavà', 'clavà', 'num masculin', 'noun', 'barn, hay barn, hay loft, stable, etc.', 'barn, hay barn, hay loft, stable', 'clavau', 'clavau', 'clavo', 'clavo', 'clavo', 'clavo', 'talvo', 'talvo', 'tablà', 'tablà', 'Barn, hay loft:\nIn the Engadin, the \"tavlo\"/\"tablà\" is the place where hay is kept. Traditionally, this was usually part of a large multi-functional farm building (i.e. a hay loft). On more modern farms, it is often a separate building (i.e. a barn).\nIn Surselva, for instance, the tradition is different. The \"clavau\" is always a separate building and not part of the farmhouse. The term may apply to either the whole building (including both the part for stabling animals and the part for storing hay). The term is also applied restrictively to the upper part of the building, i.e. the hay loft.', '', '', '', '', 1354),
