('', '', 1, 0, 0, 'cletg', 'cletg', 'num masculin', 'noun', 'luck, stroke of luck', 'luck, stroke of luck', 'cletg', 'cletg', 'cletg', 'cletg', 'cletg', 'cletg', '-----', '', '-----', '', 'Expressions with \"avair\":\nRomansh has numerous expressions with \"avair\" (\"have\") plus a noun that correspond to English expressions with \"be\" plus an adjective. In this instance: to \"be lucky\" is \"avair fortuna\" or \"avair cletg\" (\"have luck\"). In this sense, \"cletg\" (which is not used in all the idioms) is a synonym of \"fortuna\". \"Fortuna also means \"fortune\" in the sense of \"wealth\". \"Cletg\" means luck in general or a single stoke of luck', '', '', '', '', 1361),
