('', '1', 0, 0, 1, 'encreschadetgna', 'encreschadetgna', 'num feminin', 'noun', 'homesickness, longing', 'homesickness, longing', 'encarschadetgna', 'encarschadetgna', 'ancarschadetgna, carschadetgna', 'ancarschadetgna, carschadetgna', 'ancreschadetna, malancuneia', 'ancreschadetna, malancuneia', 'increschantüna', 'increschantüna', 'increschantüm', 'increschantüm', 'Homesickness, longing for home:\nA longing to be back home is at the heart of Romansh feelings and is reflected in numerous writings and songs.\nAsking travellers if they long to be home or if they feel homesick is almost as much a part of Romansh conversation as is the weather in the English-speaking world!\nThe subject of \"encreschadetgna\" is not new. It has roots deep in history. In the poor regions of Romansh-speaking Graubünden the rural economy was only ever able to support a limited population, and many people simply had to go elsewhere for a period of time or even for good to find the merest of livelihoods.\nNote the verbal expression \"Laschas ti encrescher?\" (\"Do you feel homesick?\" - literally: \"do you allow a feeling of homesickness to arise?\")\n(See also the note on \"swallow\" or \"randulin(a)\".)', '', '', '', '', 2293),
