('', '', 0, 0, 0, 'lain', 'lain', 'num masculin', 'noun', 'wood, timber', 'wood, timber', 'lenn', 'lenn', 'len', 'len', 'lenn', 'lenn', 'lain', 'lain', 'lain', 'lain', 'Wood(en:)\n\"Wooden\" or \"made of wood/timber is \"da laina\".', 'Lain(a):\n\"Da laina\" è \"wooden\" u \"made of wood/timber\".\nIns fa normalmain adiever da \"timber\" enstagl da \"wood\" per plantas derschidas u laina sco material da construcziun.\nL\'indstria da laina è \"timber industry\".', '', '', '', 3452),
('', '', 0, 0, 0, 'laina', 'laina', 'num feminin', 'noun', 'wood, timber', 'wood, timber', 'lenna', 'lenna', 'lena', 'lena', 'lenna', 'lenna', 'laina', 'laina', 'laina', 'laina', 'Collective feminine nouns in Romansh:\nRomansh has numerous masculine nouns that not only have a normal plural in \"-s\" but a collective form too (a feminine singular noun formed by adding an \"a\" and possibly doubling the final consonant). No absolutely hard-and-fast rule can be given for the use of the two forms.\nIn the case of \"lain\", the normal plural in \"s\" is rarely used. The collective form (\"laina\") is used frequently for \"timber\" or \"felled trees\".', 'Lain(a):\n\"Da laina\" è \"wooden\" u \"made of wood/timber\".\nIns fa normalmain adiever da \"timber\" enstagl da \"wood\" per plantas derschidas u laina sco material da construcziun.\nL\'indstria da laina è \"timber industry\".', '', '', '', 3453),
