('', '1', 1, 0, 1, 'duvrar', 'duvrar', 'verb', 'verb', 'use, need', 'use, need', 'duvrar\n(jeu drovel)', 'duvrar, drovan, drovel', 'duvrar', 'duvrar, dovr, duragn, dovra, duvrad', 'duvrar', 'duvrar, douvra', 'druver', 'druver, drouva', 'dovrar', 'dovrar, douvra', 'Romansh verbs (10):\nVerbs with a vowel change in some of their parts and the \"-el\" ending in their first person singular:\n\"Duvrar\" is one of these. To view its full conjugation, click \"Details\".\nIn Rumantsch Grischun, the first-person singular normally has no ending. Whenever the verb stem ends in a palatalised consonant, a consonant cluster or an \"i\", \"...el\" is added. There are certain border-line cases, such as this one, in which the addition of the \"-el\" ending is optional.\nIn Sursilvan, most verbs have this ending.', '', '', 'DUVRAR\n\nPreschent:\njau dovr(el)\nti dovras\nel/ella/ins dovra\nnus duvrain\nvus duvrais\nels/ellas dovran\n\nFutur:\njau vegn a duvrar\nti vegns a duvrar\nel/ella/ins vegn a duvrar\nnus vegnin a duvrar\nvus vegnis a duvrar\nels/ellas vegnan a duvrar\n\nImperfect:\njau duvrava\nti duvravas\nel/ella/ins duvrava\nnus duvravan\nvus duvravas\nels/ellas duvravan\n\nParticip perfect:\nduvrà (f: duvrada, mpl: duvrads, fpl: duvradas)\n\nPerfect:\njau hai duvrà\nti has duvrà\nel/ella/ins ha duvrà\nnus avain duvrà\nvus avais duvrà\nels/ellas han duvrà\n\nCundiziunal:\njau duvrass\nti duvrassas\nel/ella/ins duvrass\nnus duvrassan\nvus duvrassas\nels/ellas duvrassan\n\nConjunctiv:\nche jau dovria\nche ti dovrias\nch\'el/ella/ins dovria\nche nus dovrian\nche vus dovrias\nch\'els/ellas dovrian\n\nImperativ:\ndovra!\nduvrai!\n\nGerundi:\nduvrond //', '', 4163),
