('', '', 0, 0, 0, 'referendum', 'referendum', 'num masculin', 'noun', 'referendum, plebiscite', 'referendum, plebiscite', '(=RG)', 'referendum', '(=RG)', 'referendum', '(=RG)', 'referendum', '(=RG)', 'referendum', '(=RG)', 'referendum', 'Referendums:\nSwitzerland without referendums would be like Switzerland without mountains, cheese, chocolate, watches and Romansh. Unthinkable! Referendums are held at federal, cantonal and communal level.\nThere are different types:\n(1) A parliamentary decision of constitutional significance MUST be confirmed by a referendum.\n(2) Any ordinary law enacted by Parliament can be overturned in a referendum. The opponents must collect a certain number of valid signatures from registered voters within a set period of time and then win the referendum vote.\n(3) A \"popular initiative\" with sufficient support can lead to a referendum vote to enact simple legislation directly or to instruct the government (Federal Council) to submit draft legislation to parliament with a defined purpose (which is the usual case today, since most issues tend to be rather complex).\nReferendum votes are concentrated on four Sundays per year (usually in February, May, September and December) and are combined with any elections that are due. Taking all three levels, a Swiss voter will have around twenty referendum issues to decide on each year.\nTurn-out varies greatly depending on the subjects concerned.', 'Plural englais:\nNormalmain \"referendums\". Purist(a)s insisteschan sin il plural latin \"referenda\".', '', '', '', 5428),
