('', '1', 1, 0, 1, 'zambregiar', 'zambregiar', 'verb', 'verb', 'do DIY, do handicrafts, make things (as a hobby)', 'DIY, do handicrafts, make things', 'zambergiar\n(el zambregia)', 'zambergiar, zambregia', 'zambargear', 'zambargear, zambargiar, zambregiagn', 'zamberger', 'zamberger', 'zambrager', 'zambrager', 'zambriar', 'zambriar', 'Romansh verbs (9):\nVerbs with the \"-el\" ending in their first person singular:\n \"Zambregiar\" is one of these. To view its full conjugation, click \"Details\". \nIn Rumantsch Grischun, the first-person singular normally has no ending. Whenever the verb stem ends in a palatalised consonant, a consonant cluster or an \"i\", \"...el\" is added.\nIn Sursilvan, most verbs have this ending.', 'Verbs irregulars englais:\n(1)\nInfinitiv: do\nPreschent: I/we/you/they do, he/she/it/one does\nPassà simpel: did\nParticip: done\n(2)\nInfinitiv/preschent: make\nPassà simpel: made\nParticip: made\nIna da las pli grondas difficultads per glieud ch\'emprenda englais è da distinguer tranter \"do\" e \"make\", domadus signifitgeschan \"far\" en rumantsch. Il \"tun\" tudestg è normalmain \"do\". Il \"machen\" tudestg po esser \"do\" u \"make\".\nLas differentas furmas da \"do\" vegnan normalmain cumbinadas cun il negativ \"not\": \"don\'t\", \"doesn\'t\", \"didn\'t\".\nI na dat betg in pled en englais per \"zambregiar\". La meglra expressiun dependa dal context. Per exempel: per \"jau zambregel gugent\" pudess ins dir \"I like making things\".', 'El zambregia bler. = He makes lots of things; he spends a lot of time doing DIY.', '', '', 7588),
